Today, were discussing a topic that hits home literally for the estimated 1.5 million people who live in strata housing in this province. Strata corporations are legal entities whose members are the owners of the individual strata lots and common areas. These corporations and their agents are considered organizations under PIPA. While Pippa does not cover individuals actions as private citizens, it does cover the actions taken by strata corporations. Well delve into this intersection between the personal and commercial more throughout this episode. Its often said that when it comes to Strata housing, good laws make good neighbors. When we are sharing spaces with other people, with conflicting views about things like safety, finances, and even personal taste, it seemed inevitable to look at some of these issues through the lens of privacy and safeguarding personal information. We will discuss what you can do if your strata complex feels like a prison with cameras set out to police the slightest by law infraction. What should and shouldnt be included in council minutes? What about strata-related correspondence? Should you redact names or other personal information when somebody lodges a complaint? What are the privacy implications of the trend towards increased decision.

Extended fasting is when you fast longer than 48 hours. Its not to be confused with alternate day fasting, where you eat one day and fast the next, then eat the next day, then fast the following day, and so on and so forth. Extended fasting should not be confuse with alternate-day fasting, these are two very different things. Just because you only fast one full day, that is not really considered an extended fast. You really have to go beyond 40 to 48 to 72 hours and those are more known as extended fasts.
